● - What is `NPM`?
     npm is a package manager.
● - What is `Parcel/Webpack`? Why do we need it?
     Parcel\Webpack is a bundler. We need it because it helps us to bundle everything and makes the app dev and prod ready.
● - What is `.parcel-cache`
     .parcel-cache is a folder that gets created when we run npx parcel index.html. It basically caches all the files that helps in HMR.
● - What is `npx` ?
       npx is a command that we use for the execution of any npm package.
● - What is difference between `dependencies` vs `devDependencies`
      dependencies are normal dependencies that can be used in development and production. But devDependencies can only be used during development 
      phase.
